<item>
            <title>[PIG-1648] Split combination may return too many block locations to map/reduce framework</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/PIG-1648</link>
                <project id="12310730" key="PIG">Pig</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;For instance, if a small split has block locations h1, h2 and h3; another small split has h1, h3, h4. After combination, the composite split contains 4 block locations. If the number of component splits is big, then the number of block locations could be big too. In fact, the  number of block locations serves as a hint to M/R as the best hosts this composite split should be run on so the list should contain a short list, say 5, of the hosts that contain the most data in this composite split.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
